[[Gypsy]] psionicists often learned this devotion.{{Cite dragon/59/Gypsies: A curse or a blessing|18}}
===Creatures & Sentient Races===
* [[Baku]], a powerful psionic race, innately possessed a 12{{th}} degree mastery of ''animal telepathy''.<ref>
* [[Brain coral]], an intelligent and psionic range of [[coral]], innately possessed a 9{{th}} degree mastery of ''animal telepathy''.<ref>{{Cite dragon/116/The Dragon's Bestiary|38}}
* [[Planetar]]s, one of the orders of [[angel]]s in the [[multiverse]], innately possessed a 14{{th}} degree mastery of ''animal telepathy''.<ref>
* [[Solar]]s, another order of angels in the multiverse, innately possessed a 4{{th}} degree mastery of ''animal telepathy''.<ref>

===Individuals===
* [[Elrem|Elrem the Wise]], a powerful [[Uthgar]] [[shaman]] of the [[Great Worm tribe]].<ref group="note" name="shaman">''[[The North: Guide to the Savage Frontier]]'' and ''[[Powers & Pantheons]]'' both state that the "great worm" form an Uthgar shaman can [[wild shape|shapechange]] into confers a number of psionic powers. The powers listed are nearly the same as those that were originally detailed for Elrem back in ''[[The Savage Frontier]]'', thus it can be inferred that Elrem's psionic powers are not unique to him. The only power absent in both sources is ''animal telepathy''. This is presumably due to it not having made the transition from 1{{st}} to 2{{nd}} edition AD&D, rather than it being unique to Elrem in any way. Therefore, it can be further inferred that ''animal telepathy'' is likewise a power this "great worm" form confers.
* [[Illistyl Elventree]], a member of the [[Knights of Myth Drannor]].
* [[Peter Trum]].<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/49/The Living City: The For-Rest Inn|29}}

